HEADWORD: Sea corn
<hw>Sea" corn`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A yellow
cylindrical mass of egg capsules of certain species of whelks
(<gen>Buccinum</gen>), which resembles an ear of maize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

